  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "At https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/common/rlp.go#L135 a uint64 is converted to int64. This will overflow for values above 0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF (https://golang.org/ref/spec#Numeric_types)\n\nThis can for example happen if the PoW nonce is big enough: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/core/state/state_object.go#L331\n\nAfter the int64 encoding, the value is then converted to a big.Int, and .Bytes() called on it, which will convert a negative number to a positive one as it returns the absolute value: https://golang.org/pkg/math/big/#Int.Bytes\n\nNegative numbers is not a problem for RLP encoding though, as we never have negative numbers in the layer of the protocol that encodes integers using RLP.\n",
